{#
  Map phase — entity extraction from one batch of episodes.

  Variables:
    batch_index     int    0-based batch number
    mode            str    "same_lang" | "cross_lang"
    source_language str    "zh" | "en" (ISO-639-1 code of the source content)
    episode_range   str    "ep01–ep20"
    text_content    str    formatted episode text (see map_phase.py)
#}
{% if source_language == "en" %}
This is batch {{ batch_index + 1 }} of an English drama series ({{ episode_range }}).
The text below is the English ASR transcript for this episode batch.
{% elif mode == "same_lang" %}
This is batch {{ batch_index + 1 }} of a Chinese short-drama series ({{ episode_range }}).
The text below is the Chinese ASR transcript for this episode batch.
{% else %}
This is batch {{ batch_index + 1 }} of a Chinese short-drama series ({{ episode_range }}).
The text below contains paired lines from each subtitle segment:
  [OCR] = English subtitle as captured from the screen
  [ASR] = Chinese audio transcript of the same moment
{% endif %}

━━ YOUR TASK ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Extract every **recurring** character name and all forms of address used for
that character in this batch.

Rules
─────
1.  Include a name ONLY if it appears at least **twice** in the text below.
    Ignore one-off or clearly incidental mentions.
2.  The canonical name should be the most **formal or complete** form
    (e.g. "霍建华" not "建华", "Ji-hoon" not "hoon").
3.  Aliases are **every other form** the text uses to address that character
    (titles, nicknames, shortened forms).
4.  This is only a portion of the full series — do not invent names or
    relationships not present in this text.
{% if mode == "cross_lang" %}
5.  For cross_lang: map each Chinese canonical name to its English subtitle
    equivalent found in [OCR] lines.  Also list any OCR typos or variant
    spellings of the English name as ocr_en_variants.
{% endif %}

━━ OUTPUT FORMAT ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Return ONLY the following JSON — no prose, no code fences, no commentary:

{
  "characters": {
    "<canonical_name>": {
      "aliases": ["<form_1>", "<form_2>"],
      "canonical_en": "<English_name_or_null>",
      "ocr_en_variants": ["<typo_1>", "<variant_2>"]
    }
  }
}

━━ TEXT ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
{{ text_content }}
